.TH BITCOIN "1" "January 2026" "perbug v30.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
perbug \- manual page for perbug v30.2.0
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B perbug
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] \fI\,COMMAND\/\fR...
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-multiprocess\fR
Run multiprocess binaries perbug\-node, perbug\-gui.
.TP
\fB\-M\fR, \fB\-\-monolithic\fR
Run monolithic binaries perbugd, perbug\-qt. (Default behavior)
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Show version information
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show full help message
.SS "Commands:"
.TP
gui [ARGS]
Start GUI, equivalent to running 'perbug\-qt [ARGS]' or 'perbug\-gui [ARGS]'.
.TP
node [ARGS]
Start node, equivalent to running 'perbugd [ARGS]' or 'perbug\-node [ARGS]'.
.TP
rpc [ARGS]
Call RPC method, equivalent to running 'perbug\-cli \fB\-named\fR [ARGS]'.
.TP
wallet [ARGS]
Call wallet command, equivalent to running 'perbug\-wallet [ARGS]'.
.TP
tx [ARGS]
Manipulate hex\-encoded transactions, equivalent to running 'perbug\-tx [ARGS]'.
.TP
help
Show full help message.
.SS "Additional less commonly used commands:"
.TP
bench [ARGS]
Run bench command, equivalent to running 'bench_perbug [ARGS]'.
.IP
chainstate [ARGS] Run perbug kernel chainstate util, equivalent to running 'perbug\-chainstate [ARGS]'.
test [ARGS]       Run unit tests, equivalent to running 'test_perbug [ARGS]'.
test\-gui [ARGS]   Run GUI unit tests, equivalent to running 'test_perbug\-qt [ARGS]'.
